	<!-- Note schema EXPRESS are in ..\resources\resource_name\name_of_schema.xml -->
   <introduction>
   </introduction>
   <fund_cons>
	<p>
		A state represents the existence of something 
		over a period of time when it exhibits some characteristic that can 
		be identified and is distinct from other periods when that same characteristic does not apply. 
		The characteristics define a type of state and are defined using data types specified in the 
		state_type_schema. 
	</p>
	<p>
		States may be specified that are composed of multiple sub-states. They may be related by cause and effect 
		when one state causes another.
	</p>
</fund_cons>

